{
  "stem": "17821.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I never heard of anybody doing that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I also taught cheder.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "From the age of 16, I taught the five-year-olds.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in that first one year that they were with me, they learned how to read Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then they went to the next class next year, where they began to read siddur and learn further.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But for several years, from the age of 16 until I got married at the age of 22, I, I taught the-- in Hebrew school.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There wasn't much time for friendship because I, I had to be at school all day, and then a lot of homework in the evening, and my Hebrew school or teaching.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So that-- we had-- I had a couple of Jewish girls, some of my close friends.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then, when I got to a-- be 17 or 18 or so, there was a Jewish Girls Club formed by a lady-- a wealthy lady-- a Jewish lady of the town, who would have us meet once a week.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She rented a room in a building.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And one, one evening a week, the girls came.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The unfortunate thing I realized later, there were no boys.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But still, here with the girls, and she had programs.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she taught us to sing things.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we went in for musical competitions.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They would have all the groups from the center of England meeting together and, and vying for singing things that they were assigned to.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I don't see what else I can say.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She had a nephew from France because the building-- the business that-- where she got money from had something in France in Calais.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And a nephew of hers was spending some time in Nottingham.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
